summary: A couple of things I need to note after watching Detective Pikachu: The writing is actually good, and I could write you a thesis...
body:
A couple of things I need to note after watching Detective Pikachu:

  • The writing is actually good, and I could write you a thesis why.
  • The special effects of course are awesome! (especially the Pokemon, I was fangirling all the time over fur and stuff like that)
  • The Pokemon are all adorable and I gotta catch adopt them all (Even Mr.Mime, he’s not cute, but he’s interesting)
  • I jokingly guessed one of the later plot twist 30 minutes into the movie when I had no clues to that sort of development (I did the same with Gintama…)
  • The story is simple but interesting, the concept for the “villain” is nice
  • I want another movie in the same universe, it doesn’t have to be a sequel!

Go watch the movie, it’s so good!

summary: In Super Mario 64, jumping toward a Tox Box in Shifting Sand Land during a precise point of its movement in the manner depicted...
caption:
In Super Mario 64, jumping toward a Tox Box in Shifting Sand Land during a precise point of its movement in the manner depicted will result in Mario instantly dying. Mario will play the animation of sinking into quicksand despite being in mid-air; this is merely one of several different ways quicksand can kill Mario remotely, another being punching near a ledge, as seen in this post.
